sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as gRPC Client
    participant Channel as gRPC Channel<br/>(HTTP/2)
    participant Server as gRPC Server
    participant Backend as Backend Service<br/>(Processing Engine)

    Note over Client,Backend: gRPC Bidirectional Streaming - Real-time Sensor Data Processing

    rect rgb(235, 240, 255)
        Note over Client,Server: Phase 1 - Channel Establishment
        Client->>Channel: Open HTTP/2 Connection (TLS 1.3)
        Channel->>Server: TCP Handshake + ALPN Negotiation
        Server-->>Channel: SETTINGS Frame (max_concurrent_streams: 100)
        Channel-->>Client: Channel Ready
        Client->>Channel: Send Request Headers<br/>POST /sensor.SensorService/StreamProcessing<br/>content-type: application/grpc
        Channel->>Server: Open Bidirectional Stream (stream_id: 1)
        Server-->>Channel: Response Headers (200 OK)
        Server->>Backend: Initialize Processing Pipeline
        Backend-->>Server: Pipeline Ready
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 235)
        Note over Client,Backend: Phase 2 - Bidirectional Streaming (concurrent send/receive)

        par Client Streaming (requests)
            Client->>Channel: DATA Frame: SensorReading {device: "temp-01", value: 72.5, ts: 1001}
            Channel->>Server: Forward SensorReading
            Server->>Backend: Process Reading (temp-01)
        and Server Streaming (responses)
            Backend-->>Server: Analysis Result (temp-01: NORMAL)
            Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: ProcessedResult {device: "temp-01", status: NORMAL, anomaly_score: 0.12}
            Channel-->>Client: Receive ProcessedResult
        end

        Client->>Channel: DATA Frame: SensorReading {device: "pressure-03", value: 185.2, ts: 1002}
        Channel->>Server: Forward SensorReading
        Server->>Backend: Process Reading (pressure-03)
        Backend-->>Server: ALERT: Anomaly Detected!
        Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: ProcessedResult {device: "pressure-03", status: ALERT, anomaly_score: 0.94}
        Channel-->>Client: Receive ProcessedResult (ALERT)

        Note over Client: Client adjusts sampling rate based on alert

        Client->>Channel: DATA Frame: SensorReading {device: "pressure-03", value: 187.8, ts: 1003}
        Client->>Channel: DATA Frame: SensorReading {device: "pressure-03", value: 191.0, ts: 1004}
        Client->>Channel: DATA Frame: SensorReading {device: "temp-01", value: 73.1, ts: 1005}

        Note over Server,Backend: Server batches and processes readings

        Channel->>Server: Forward 3 SensorReadings
        Server->>Backend: Batch Process (3 readings)
        Backend-->>Server: Batch Results Ready
        Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: ProcessedResult {device: "pressure-03", status: CRITICAL, trend: RISING}
        Channel-->>Client: Receive ProcessedResult (CRITICAL)
        Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: ProcessedResult {device: "pressure-03", status: CRITICAL, action: SHUTDOWN_RECOMMENDED}
        Channel-->>Client: Receive ProcessedResult (ACTION)
        Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: ProcessedResult {device: "temp-01", status: NORMAL}
        Channel-->>Client: Receive ProcessedResult
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 220)
        Note over Client,Backend: Phase 3 - Flow Control
        Note over Channel: HTTP/2 Flow Control Window Exhausted
        Channel-->>Client: WINDOW_UPDATE needed (stream_id: 1)
        Client->>Channel: WINDOW_UPDATE (increment: 65535)
        Note over Channel: Flow control window replenished
        Channel->>Server: WINDOW_UPDATE forwarded

        Note over Server,Backend: Server-side backpressure
        Server->>Channel: Pause receiving (processing lag)
        Note over Channel: Buffering client frames
        Server->>Backend: Drain processing queue
        Backend-->>Server: Queue drained
        Server->>Channel: Resume receiving
        Channel->>Server: Flush buffered frames
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over Client,Backend: Phase 4 - Graceful Shutdown
        Client->>Channel: END_STREAM flag (client done sending)
        Channel->>Server: Client half-close (no more requests)
        Note over Server,Backend: Process remaining buffered readings
        Server->>Backend: Flush pipeline
        Backend-->>Server: Final summary statistics
        Server-->>Channel: DATA Frame: StreamSummary {total: 5, alerts: 2, critical: 1, avg_latency_ms: 12}
        Channel-->>Client: Receive StreamSummary
        Server-->>Channel: END_STREAM flag + Trailers (grpc-status: 0, grpc-message: OK)
        Channel-->>Client: Stream Complete (status: OK)
        Note over Client,Channel: HTTP/2 stream closed, channel available for reuse
    end
